                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Reduce cognitive load to maximize deep work.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 4. Meet the Agents -->
        <section id="meet-the-agents" class="section-card">
            <h2 class="section-title text-center gradient-text">4. Meet the Agents: Your Dedicated AI Product Team</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">Our system comprises six specialized AI agents, each handling a critical phase of personal project management, forming a cohesive and intelligent product team.</p>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <div class="agent-card">
                    <span class="agent-icon text-blue-600">✍️</span>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl text-blue-800 mb-2">Agent 1: The Personal Assistant</h4>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-gray-700">(The Scrivener)</p>
                    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4 list-disc list-inside">
                        <li>**Role:** Rapid thought capture & notification.</li>
                        <li>**Value:** Eliminates ideation friction.</li>
                        <li>**Analogy:** Your ever-present digital notepad.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="agent-card">
                    <span class="agent-icon text-yellow-600">🏛️</span>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl text-yellow-800 mb-2">Agent 2: The Organizer</h4>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-gray-700">(The Architect)</p>
                    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4 list-disc list-inside">
                        <li>**Role:** Structures raw inputs, categorizes.</li>
                        <li>**Value:** Transforms ideas into actionable tasks.</li>
                        <li>**Analogy:** Skilled project coordinator.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="agent-card">
                    <span class="agent-icon text-green-600">🧭</span>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl text-green-800 mb-2">Agent 3: The Executive Function</h4>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-gray-700">(The Strategist)</p>
                    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4 list-disc list-inside">
                        <li>**Role:** Consolidates, prioritizes workload.</li>
                        <li>**Value:** Overcomes "tool fatigue," guides focus.</li>
                        <li>**Analogy:** Your internal CEO.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="agent-card">
                    <span class="agent-icon text-purple-600">💻</span>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl text-purple-800 mb-2">Agent 4: The Dev Team Leader</h4>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-gray-700">(The Executor)</p>
                    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4 list-disc list-inside">
                        <li>**Role:** Executes coding, generates content.</li>
                        <li>**Value:** Automates "hands-on keyboard" work.</li>
                        <li>**Analogy:** Efficient autonomous lead developer.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="agent-card">
                    <span class="agent-icon text-red-600">✅</span>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl text-red-800 mb-2">Agent 5: The Sanity Checker</h4>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-gray-700">(The QA Lead)</p>
                    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4 list-disc list-inside">
                        <li>**Role:** Reviews work, suggests tests, ensures closure.</li>
                        <li>**Value:** Crucial quality gate.</li>
                        <li>**Analogy:** Your vigilant QA engineer.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="agent-card">
                    <span class="agent-icon text-indigo-600">🧘</span>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl text-indigo-800 mb-2">Agent 6: The Retro Agent</h4>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-gray-700">(The Philosopher / Coach)</p>
                    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4 list-disc list-inside">
                        <li>**Role:** Facilitates retrospectives, journaling.</li>
                        <li>**Value:** Drives continuous improvement.</li>
                        <li>**Analogy:** Reflective mentor and archivist.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 5. Project Roadmap -->
        <section id="project-roadmap" class="section-card">
            <h2 class="section-title text-center gradient-text">5. Project Roadmap: Iterative Delivery for Tangible Value</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">Adopting an agile, iterative approach to ensure rapid MVP delivery and continuous value realization.</p>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-b-4 border-blue-500">
                    <h3 class="sub-title text-blue-700">Phase 1: Brain Dump & Basic Organization (MVP - 1 Week Target)</h3>
                    <p class="text-md text-gray-700 mb-4">Establishing foundational input and initial AI-driven structuring.</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm space-y-2">
                        <li>**Goal:** Core capture, initial AI processing, Google Tasks/Keep integration.</li>
                        <li>**Focus:** Agent 1 & initial Agent 2 logic. AWS Free Tier validation.</li>
                        <li>**Deliverables:** Simple web input, raw thought processing, task creation in Google Tasks/Keep.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-purple-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-b-4 border-purple-500">
                    <h3 class="sub-title text-purple-700">Phase 2: Executive Function & Consolidated View</h3>
                    <p class="text-md text-gray-700 mb-4">Introducing core prioritization and a unified task dashboard.</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm space-y-2">
                        <li>**Goal:** Holistic workload view and prioritization.</li>
                        <li>**Focus:** Agent 3 development, Firestore integration.</li>
                        <li>**Deliverables:** Prioritized "master list" dashboard.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-b-4 border-green-500">
                    <h3 class="sub-title text-green-700">Phase 3: Dev Team Leader & Initial GitHub Automation</h3>
                    <p class="text-md text-gray-700 mb-4">Automating GitHub project and issue creation directly from the system.</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm space-y-2">
                        <li>**Goal:** Streamlined coding project initiation.</li>
                        <li>**Focus:** Agent 4 development, secure GitHub API integration.</li>
                        <li>**Deliverables:** Ability to convert structured tasks into GitHub issues/projects.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-red-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-b-4 border-red-500">
                    <h3 class="sub-title text-red-700">Phase 4: Sanity Checker & Retrospective Agents</h3>
                    <p class="text-md text-gray-700 mb-4">Implementing quality assurance and continuous learning loops.</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm space-y-2">
                        <li>**Goal:** Post-completion review, learning, and archiving.</li>
                        <li>**Focus:** Agent 5 & 6 development.</li>
                        <li>**Deliverables:** Automated review suggestions, structured retrospectives, archival system.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-inner mt-12 text-center">
                <h3 class="sub-title text-gray-700">Future Enhancements: Scaling Our Intelligence</h3>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">Long-term strategic initiatives to further enhance system capabilities:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-md mt-4 inline-block text-left">
                    <li>Deep GitHub Copilot integration for automated branch creation & code commits.</li>
                    <li>Advanced user testing scenarios generated by Agent 5.</li>
                    <li>Expansion of integrations (e.g., finance, health data).</li>
                    <li>The Agent 6 "secret easter egg" for winding down.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 6. Technical Foundations -->
        <section id="technical-foundations" class="section-card">
            <h2 class="section-title text-center gradient-text">6. Technical Foundations & Resource Strategy</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">A robust, scalable, and cost-efficient architecture to power your personal AI-Ops system.</p>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="sub-title">Core Technology Stack</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-lg space-y-3 pl-4">
                        <li>**Cloud Platform:** AWS (Lambda for agents, API Gateway for access, S3/CloudFront for frontend).</li>
                        <li>**Database:** Firestore (Google Cloud) - for flexible, real-time NoSQL data.</li>
                        <li>**AI Engine:** Gemini API (`gemini-2.0-flash`) - for core NLU/NLG and reasoning.</li>
                        <li>**Integrations:** GitHub API, Google Tasks API, Google Keep API.</li>
                        <li>**Authentication:** Firebase Authentication - for secure user access.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="sub-title">Resource Strategy: Leveraging Free Tiers</h3>
                    <div class="highlight-box mb-4">
                        <p class="font-bold text-lg text-blue-700">AWS Free Tier & Google Cloud Free Tier:</p>
                        <p class="text-md text-gray-700">Generally **sufficient for MVP and ongoing personal use**, provided usage remains within limits (e.g., millions of Lambda requests, GBs of storage).</p>
                    </div>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-lg space-y-3 pl-4">
                        <li>**Cost Efficiency:** Strategic use of free tiers to minimize operational overhead.</li>
                        <li>**Security:** Emphasis on secure API key management (AWS Secrets Manager) and robust authentication.</li>
                        <li>**Scalability:** Cloud-native architecture ensures future scalability if needed.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

